        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45589",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\r\n$macLockedComment->getLabel()->setAttrib('style', 'display: none'); \r\n{quote}\r\nVery bad idea! The method \"getLabel\" returns the content of the label.\r\n\r\n[API-Doc: Zend_Form_Element::getLabel()|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_Form\/Element\/Zend_Form_Element.html#getLabel]\r\n\r\nYou can use the decorator:\r\n{code}\r\n$form->getElement('foo')->getDecorator('label')->setOption('style', 'display: none;');\r\n{code}\r\nThis is not a workaround, this is the normal behaviour!\r\n\r\nThis is not a bug!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-24T09:34:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-24T09:34:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45593",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I know that this is the normal behaviour.\r\n\r\nThis line should have been only a suggestion for implementing it.\r\n\r\nBecause the label itself is a own object, there should be a possibility to change it over the object, not the decorator - IMO\r\n\r\nBut thanks for the solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thadafinser",
                        "name": "thadafinser",
                        "displayName": "Martin Keckeis",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-24T18:08:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-24T18:10:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45594",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\r\nBecause the label itself is a own object, there should be a possibility to change it over the object, not the decorator - IMO\r\n{quote}\r\nAll elements from Zend_Form represents objects with which a user can interact. This is not an invention or an idea from the Zend Framework. It corresponds to the W3C HTML standard.\r\nThese special elements are called \"controls\":\r\n\r\n[HTML4: 17 Forms - 17.1 Introduction to forms|http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html401\/interact\/forms.html#h-17.1]\r\n[HTML4: 17 Forms - 17.2 Controls|http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html401\/interact\/forms.html#h-17.2]\r\n\r\nControl types are:\r\n\r\n* buttons\r\n* checkboxes\r\n* radio buttons\r\n* menus\r\n* text input\r\n* file select\r\n* hidden controls\r\n* object controls\r\n\r\nA label element is used to specify labels for controls, but itself it is not a control!\r\n\r\n[HTML4: 17 Forms - 17.9 Labels|http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html401\/interact\/forms.html#h-17.9]\r\n\r\nI see no reason why Zend_Form deviate from the HTML standard. (Also HTML5 brings no change here.)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-24T19:58:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-24T19:58:16.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
